commit.message:
Ignore trailing graphs.

Fixes https://github.com/jrfonseca/xdot.py/issues/112
github: Use actions/checkout@v3.
Add argument name to Gtk.Window.new()
Use GObject.SignalFlags.RUN_LAST instead of GObject.SIGNAL_RUN_LAST

Minor bugfix for empty search

The label showing the number of search results is now cleared when the user deletes an old search query
Keep XDotParser importable from old location

Leverage PEP 562 for backwards compatibility.

As suggested https://github.com/jrfonseca/xdot.py/issues/108#issuecomment-1245552802
Split XDotParser into ui.

Allow to use xdot.dot headlessly.

https://github.com/jrfonseca/xdot.py/issues/108

Fix test.py
github-actions: Test both on Ubuntu 20.04 and 22.04.
Add tooltips to various toolbar buttons.

return xdotcode anyway

Be more tolerate. Return dot output if any, even there was an error.
Bind "W" key to zoom_to_fit.

Remove unnecessary max_length from text search.

With this commit it's now possible to search text of any length.
Set PNG to default export format and add more formats
Introduce "Export to other format" feature

Support gv extensions in file chooser

The project switched to that since *.dot is taken by Microsoft Word:
https://marc.info/?l=graphviz-devel&m=129418103126092

Fix tooltip on Wayland

On Wayland, the following is logged into console and no tooltip is visible or it is displayed at the top left:

    Gdk-Message: 06:04:40.431: Window 0x252d550 is a temporary window without parent, application will not be able to position it on screen.

Fix WM_CLASS.

Under Manjaro and Pop_OS, the class was set to "-m" when xdot was run
this way:

  python3 -m xdot foo

This solution was suggested by Moritz Meier.
